@node Introduction

2. Introduction
ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ
LoadModule is a program for installing resident modules, by
using the KickMem and KickTag lists in ExecBase.

I made LoadModule so I could load scsi.device before
softkicking KS 2.04, and that way use the harddrive in my
A1200 even under KS 2.04. If you want to try this, I have
also made a program that extracts scsi.device from KS 3.0
(Aminet:util/boot/GetSCSI). (KS means Kickstart.)

Another reason for LoadModule was to try hackdisk.device by
Dan Babcock (Aminet:disk/misc/hackdisk or Fish 803), and
betaversions of scsi.device and FastFileSystem (V43) from
Amiga Technologies GmbH/Amiga International, Inc.
(ftp.amiga.de:pub/Public/PublicBETA/).

Features:
· Load module in fast memory!
· Load multiple modules at once.
· Check if module is corrupt at reboot.
· Handles files with any number of segments (of course).
· Handles files containing multiple modules (not usual).
· AmigaOS 1.2/1.3 compatible.


@endnode
@node Requirements

3. Requirements
ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ
LoadModule requires AmigaOS 1.2 or higher.

Arp.library is required on AmigaOS 1.2/1.3.


@endnode
@node Usage

4. Usage
ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ
LoadModule cannot be used from Workbench. It is pure and can
be made resident (with C:Resident). The CLI usage is:

NAME/A/M,QUIET/S,REBOOT/S,REMOVE/S,INIT/S,CHECK/S,FAST/S,
LMPRI/N,AUTOINIT/N,CLASS/N,VERSION/N,TYPE/N,PRI/N


Examples:

LoadModule DEVS:fastfilesystem DEVS:a300.ld.strip CHECK FAST

This loads betaversions of FastFileSystem and scsi.device.
They will be loaded in fast memory, and checked at every
reboot to ensure they are not corrupt.

LoadModule LIBS:*.library INIT FAST CLASS=0

Makes all libraries in LIBS: resident. INIT will
initialize the libraries (else they will have to be loaded
again when needed). CLASS=0 means that a library will not
be initialized after reboot until someone asks for it (some
would else cause the System Request "Please insert volume
ENV in any drive" to pop up).


Explanation of options:

Note that none of the options has any affect on modules that
already have been loaded by LoadModule (except REMOVE). INIT
and the last five options can lead to crashes if they aren't
used properly.

NAME
Name of module to install.

QUIET
Don't say module is installed.

REBOOT
Reboot after installing module.

REMOVE
Remove installed module.
     The full pathname can be used, but filename only is
enough. If you use "" for NAME, all modules installed by
LoadModule will be removed.
     Note that the memory a module occupied will not be
freed. The only way to get it back is to reboot.

INIT
Call exec.library/InitResident(), with the module as
argument.

CHECK
At every boot, the memory the module is loaded in will
be checked to see if it has changed. If it has, an alert
will be displayed.
     Of course LoadModule can't know if a module writes some
data to itself, simply do not use the CHECK option for them.

FAST
Loads the module in best memory available, which on many
systems means fast memory instead of chip memory.
     To accomplish this the module is loaded in best memory
available, but the memory will not be referenced in the
KickMem list. Instead an extra tag is installed that
allocates the memory when the machine reboots. Also the
resident module tag structure is relocated to the type of
memory Exec can access when it builds the list of resident
modules.

LMPRI
If the CHECK and/or FAST options are used, LoadModule will
install its own resident tag. This sets the priority of it.
     By default it is two less than the priority of
intuition.library, so alerts can be displayed if memory for
the module can't be allocated, or if it has changed.
     After an alert, the variables in ExecBase that hold
information about resident things are cleared (i.e.
ColdCapture, CoolCapture, WarmCapture, KickTagPtr and
KickMemPtr), and then the machine is rebooted again.

AUTOINIT
Use zero (0) to clear the flag RTF_AUTOINIT in the rt_Flags
field of the resident module tag structure, one (1) to set
the flag.

CLASS
This will be put in the rt_Flags field of the resident
module tag structure (RTF_AUTOINIT will not be changed).
These are the flags from include:exec/resident.[h|i]:
RTF_COLDSTART  = 1
RTF_SINGLETASK = 2 (KS 2.0+)
RTF_AFTERDOS   = 4 (KS 2.0+)

VERSION
Will be put in the rt_Version field of the resident module
tag structure.

TYPE
Put this in the rt_Type field of the resident module tag
structure.
Here are common definitions from include:exec/nodes.[h|i]:
NT_UNKNOWN  = 0
NT_DEVICE   = 3
NT_RESOURCE = 8
NT_LIBRARY  = 9

PRI
Set priority in the rt_Pri field of the resident module tag
structure.


@endnode
@node History

5. History
ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ
1.0 (23.7.97)
· First release.

1.1 (21.8.97)
· CHECK option always complained if LoadModule changed
  anything in the resident module tag structure.
· REMOVE option will never free memory for the extra
  resident tag LoadModule installs. It was a bug when any
  of the modules had been installed with the FAST option.


